cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

The paper discusses the performance of deep ResNets compared to linear predictors, which is a topic related to machine learning and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the Hessian matrix and critical points, which are concepts related to optimization and numerical analysis, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of ResNets in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of near-identity regions, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
